==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instrumentality
<hw>In`stru*men*tal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Instrumentalities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<def>The quality or condition of being instrumental; that which is
instrumental; anything used as a means; medium; agency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>instrumentality</qex> of faith in justification.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The discovery of gunpowder developed the science of attack and
defense in a new <qex>instrumentality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J. H.
Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instrumentally</ent>⟦br⟧
